      \begin {tikzcd}
        \mu  \ar [d, mapsto, "\lambda _j"']\ar [r, mapsto, "\lambda _k"] & \mu _k(*)\ar [d, equals, "?"] \\
        \mu _j(*)\ar [r, mapsto, "Df"'] & Df(\mu _j(*))\makebox [0pt][l]{,}
      \end {tikzcd}


which holds because \mu  is a cone.

In pictures, a 2-simplex \sigma  may be drawn as:





